Pseudocode:
"A" for exam grades greater than or equal to 90, "B" for grades 80 to 89, "C" for grades 70 to 79,
   "D" for grades 60 to 69 and "F" for all other grades.

This pseudocode may be written in C++ as;
   if (studentGrade >= 90) {
      cout << "A";
   }
   else {
      if (studentGrade >= 80) {
         cout << "B";
      }
      else {
         if (studentGrade >= 70) {
            cout << "C";
         }
         else {
            if (studentGrade >= 60 {
               cout << "D";
            }
            else {
               cout << "F";
            }
         }
      }
   }

以下形式避免向右深度縮編程式，在整個文字中，用大括號和括號控制宣告正文({和})，避免了稱為"dangling-else"問題的邏輯錯誤

if (studentGrade >= 90) {
   cout << "A";
}
else if (studentGrade >= 80) {
   cout << "B";
}
else if (studentGrade >= 70) {
   cout << "C";
}
else if (studentGrade >= 60) {
   cout << "D";
}
else {
   cout << "F";
}
